  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If a Keycard without metadata is used (which should be the case only if an old Keycard is being used) then we need to set metadata for that Keycard based on the app state for the key stored on that Keycard.\r\n\r\nWe should do that silently when a user provides a PIN for a Keycard for any reason.\r\n\r\nAlso at this moment, some flows require a Keycard that contains metadata, thus we need to check all flows we have and let the user run any of them regardless if a Keycard contains metadata or not, but in case it doesn't contain them we need to set them firstly before we continue with the flow.",
